> [4.1.1. ](https://datarightplus.github.io/datarightplus-sharing-arrangement-v2/draft-authors-datarightplus-sharing-arrangement-v2.html#section-4.1.1)[Request Object](https://datarightplus.github.io/datarightplus-sharing-arrangement-v2/draft-authors-datarightplus-sharing-arrangement-v2.html#name-request-object)
The request object submitted to the authorisation server:
SHALL require an ID Token claim urn:dio:action_id referencing a valid Action Identifier;
SHALL reject requests containing a urn:dio:action_id claim that is unknown, expired or not associated with the requesting Initiator;

4.1.1 states that authorisation server SHALL reject expired data sharing requests, but spec does not advise a reasonable timeframe for data sharing request expiry
